explanation: This solution uses a binary search approach to efficiently guess the number. It maintains a search space of [left, right] and repeatedly divides it in half until the target number is found. The time complexity is O(log n) because each guess reduces the search space by half. The space complexity is O(1) because only a constant amount of space is used to store the search space boundaries.

